## Domain-Specific Patterns

### For Game Projects: Entity Component System (ECS)

**When to use**: Games with multiple entity types

**Structure**:
```
/entities
  ├── Entity.js          # Base entity container
  └── EntityFactory.js   # Creates configured entities
/components
  ├── HealthComponent.js
  ├── PositionComponent.js
  ├── VelocityComponent.js
  └── [Feature]Component.js
/systems
  ├── MovementSystem.js  # Processes Position + Velocity
  ├── HealthSystem.js    # Processes Health
  └── RenderSystem.js    # Processes Render components
```

**Configuration-driven**:
```javascript
// Define entities via config, not classes
const ENTITY_TYPES = {
  BASIC_ENEMY: {
    components: {
      health: { max: 100 },
      movement: { speed: 2 },
      render: { sprite: 'enemy', size: 32 }
    }
  }
};
```

**Benefits**:
- Easy to add new entity types (just config)
- No class per entity type
- Flexible behavior combinations

