## Performance Patterns

### Object Pooling

**Use for**: Frequently created/destroyed objects

**Examples**: Particles, projectiles, temporary effects

**Implementation**:
```javascript
class ObjectPool {
  constructor(factory, reset) {
    this.available = [];
    this.factory = factory;
    this.reset = reset;
  }
  
  acquire() {
    return this.available.pop() || this.factory();
  }
  
  release(obj) {
    this.reset(obj);
    this.available.push(obj);
  }
}

// Usage
const projectilePool = new ObjectPool(
  () => new Projectile(),
  (p) => p.reset()
);
```

### Canvas Optimization

**Static element caching**:
```javascript
// Create off-screen canvas
this.staticCanvas = document.createElement('canvas');
this.staticCtx = this.staticCanvas.getContext('2d');

// Render once
renderStatic(this.staticCtx);

// In render loop, just copy (fast!)
ctx.drawImage(this.staticCanvas, 0, 0);
```

**When to optimize**:
- Performance issues identified
- Many objects created/destroyed
- Complex repeated rendering

**When NOT to optimize**:
- Before performance is a problem
- Code not yet working correctly
- Would significantly complicate code

