## Before You Start Coding

### Checklist
- [ ] Check `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md` index - find relevant section
- [ ] Read relevant architecture section (e.g., `04-component-responsibilities.md`)
- [ ] Confirm file sizes - will this push anything over 400 lines?
- [ ] Check config - are there repeated values?
- [ ] Understand pattern - event-driven or direct injection?
- [ ] Plan structure - how will this integrate?

### When Unsure

Ask before implementing:
- "Should this be a new system or added to existing [system]?"
- "Should this communicate via events or direct calls?"
- "This will add [N] lines to [file]. Should I refactor first?"

---

## Success Metrics

Architecture is healthy if:
- ✅ Files stay under 400 lines
- ✅ Systems are loosely coupled
- ✅ New features easy to add
- ✅ Changes don't break unrelated features
- ✅ Architecture docs stay up-to-date
- ✅ Code is testable

If not, let's discuss architectural improvements.
